        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 3:51PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 350 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Yosemite Valley, or 23 miles southwest of Twin Lakes,
moving west at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Porcupine Flat Campground, White Wolf Campground, May Lake High
Sierra Camp, Snow Flat, Yosemite Creek Campground, Tenaya Lake, and
Rancheria Falls Wilderness Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
